subSubSection.paragraph:
Dimorphostylis brevicarpus
also resembles
D. cornigera
Harada, 1960
, from the Izu Peninsula, but can be distinguished from the latter by ( 1 ) dorsolateral carina ending anteriorly in 2–3 prominent teeth (ending of the carina not well defined in
D. cornigera
), ( 2 ) pereopod 2 carpus shorter than combined length of propodus and dactylus (longer than combined length of propodus and dactylus in
D. cornigera
), ( 3 ) uropod peduncle less than 3 times pleonite 6 length ( 3 times as long as pleonite 6 in
D. cornigera
), ( 4 ) uropod endopod 2 nd and 3 rd articles with 2 spiniform setae on inner margin ( 1 spiniform seta in
D. cornigera
), and ( 5 ) telson shorter than pleonite 6 (subequal to pleonite 6 in
D. cornigera
).
